entries.journal_entry_description: One way or another, find out what the Darkwalkers took from the crashed shuttle.
entries.journal_entry_title: Find Out What the Darkwalkers Took from the Crashed Shuttle
entries.task00_journal_entry_description: Go to the shuttleport and use the shipping terminal there to find out what was stolen from the empty crate at the crash site.
entries.task00_journal_entry_title: Use the Shipping Terminal for the Shuttle's Inventory
entries.task01_message_box_text: Unfortunately, there are no records available of what the crashed shuttle was carrying. You'll have to go to the source of the problem -- the Darkwalkers themselves.
entries.task02_journal_entry_description: Attack Darkwalker technicks and find out if they know anything about the contents of the emptied crate.
entries.task03_journal_entry_description: The technicks didn't know anything. Try attacking Darkwalker systols.
entries.task04_journal_entry_description: The systols were a dead end as well. Maybe Darkwalker triops will be a better source of information.
entries.task05_message_box_text: From a Darkwalker triop, you learn that they took a bio-scanner from the crashed shuttle, and that they shot down the shuttle in order to get this bio-scanner.
entries.task06_journal_entry_description: Return to Tanoa and let her know that the Darkwalkers took a bio-scanner. That's what had been inside the empty crate.
